rs from Madhya Pradesh]]\n[[Category:Indian women diplomats]]\n[[Category:Members of the National Cadet Corps (India)]]\n[[Category:Narendra Modi ministry]]\n[[Category:Indian Hindus]]\n[[Category:State funerals in India]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Padma Vibhushan in public affairs]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Indian politician}}\n{{EngvarB|date=April 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name = Sushma Swaraj\n| office = [[Ministry of External Affairs (India)|Minister of External Affairs]]\n| image = Sushma Swaraj Ji.jpg\n| caption = Sushma Swaraj in 2018\n| predecessor = [[Salman Khurshid]]\n| primeminister = [[Narendra Modi]]\n| successor = [[Subrahmanyam Jaishankar]]\n| office2 = [[Leader of the Opposition (India)|Leader of the Opposition in the Lok Sabha]]\n| predecessor2 = [[L. K. Advani]]\n| party = [[Bharatiya Janata Party]]\n| office1 = [[Ministry of Overseas Indian Affairs|Minister of Overseas Indian Affairs]]\n| predecessor1 = [[Vayalar Ravi]]\n| primeminister1 = [[Narendra Modi]]\n| successor1 = ''Position abolished''\n| successor2 = Vacant\n| birth_name = Sushma Sharma\n| birth_date = {{birth date|df=y|1952|2|14}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://loksabhaph.nic.in/Members/MemberBioprofile.aspx?mpsno=3812&lastls=16 | title=Lok Sabha Members Bioprofile Sushma Swaraj | publisher=[[Lok Sabha]] | accessdate=7 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.livemint.com/politics/news/remembering-sushma-swaraj-first-full-time-female-foreign-minister-to-twitter-s-favorite-1565150051427.html |title=Remembering Sushma Swaraj: First female foreign minister to Twitter's favorite |last=Roche |first=Elizabeth |date=7 August 2019 |website=Livemint |access-date=7 August 2019}}</ref>\n| birth_place = [[Ambala Cantonment]], [[East Punjab|Punjab]], [[India]]<br/>(now in [[Haryana]], [[India]])\n| death_date = {{death date and age|df=y|2019|8|6|1952|2|14}}\n| death_place = [[New Delhi]], [[Delhi]], [[India]]\n| death_cause = [[C